categories: Category:Vader Immortal: A Star Wars VR Series voice actors

nodes.text: Maya Khabira Rudolph (born July 27, 1972) is an American actress, voice actress, comedian and singer best-known for being a regular cast member of the NBC television series Saturday Night Live from 2000 to 2007. She is also known for her roles in movies such as 2010's Grown Ups, 2011's Bridesmaids, 2013's Grown Ups 2 and 2015's Sisters.

In Celebration Chicago 2019, Rudolph was announced to be voicing ZO-E3 in the Star Wars video game Vader Immortal: A Star Wars VR Series – Episode I, the first installment of the Vader Immortal: A Star Wars VR Series video game series, which was released on May 21, 2019.
